node.text:
In one encounter with God, everything can change. Regardless of your background or what you are going through, the God of revival and awakening is ready to meet you right where you are at.

We would love for you to join us for our 7th Annual Young Saints Conference [On-Campus and Online] on October 22-23 as we pursue a fresh encounter so that we may once again chase after all that God has in store for us. It is your destiny, as the youth of this generation, to be awakened again and carry power into the world. Speakers will include Ben Fitzgerald, Tom Crandall, and more! Worship from YS Worship.

node.title: Young Saints Conference 2021 - Revival is Now

node.text:
The Word of the Lord says God created man in His own image and called it good. God created a clear, powerful purpose for manhood. Men, true masculinity was built into your DNA. Yet for many people, it has been blurred by conflicting messages from the world around us. We live in a time where men are looking for the codebook to manhood.

At BraveCo Men's Conference, our hope is to answer your hard questions, get in the foxhole with you, restore the narrative of manhood, and release you into the masculinity you were born to carry.

Join us for our first-ever BraveCo Men’s Conference in partnership with Bethel Church, featuring speakers John Eldredge, Kris Vallotton, Brian Johnson, Danny Silk, Jason Vallotton, and Aaron Zint. This is not your typical Men’s Conference, but instead features opportunities to build a brotherhood as well as interactive experiences with professional horse trainer Todd Pierce, who will break a wild horse to demonstrate how Jesus pursues, heals, and becomes one with us as a Father.

Aug 25 - 27, 2021. Register now for in-person and online tickets at bethel.com/braveco

node.text:
Every man has key defining moments that shape him into the fullness of his calling and prepare him to walk boldly in his God-given manhood. 

Consider the life of David. Before he was a giant-killer, a poet, or the King of Israel, David was a young shepherd boy in the field with the sheep. Yet each defining moment of manhood in David’s life played a significant role in preparing him to live out the fullness of the calling as a king.

Here are a few key defining moments seen in David’s life: 

Boyhood: David lived in the house of his father and learned to operate as a son — a loved and valued son. This is a significant part of a man’s journey because this will be his identity for the rest of his life.

Cowboy: David fought off lions and bears. This stage often looks like taking risks to answer the question, “Do I have what it takes?” 

Warrior: David conquered Goliath. This phase is key as a man learns that there are things worth fighting and sacrificing for. Many of these battles may be battles of the heart — resisting the enemy’s temptations to take you down, minimize your influence, and your passion.

Lover: David became a poetic lover. This is a key defining moment in a man’s life. This stage is foremost about discovering the way of the heart and awakening the love of the Father. In order to be a good and effective leader, we must learn to love and be loved. 

Just like David, God is preparing you for the call of manhood and your God-given destiny.

Are you ready to live out the fullness of your calling and walk boldly in your God-given manhood? 

At BraveCo Men’s Conference you’ll receive tools you need to expand your capacity to lead, embrace your call as a man, and join a brotherhood. Join us for an opportunity to learn from speakers like John Eldredge, Kris Vallotton, Danny Silk, Brian Johnson, and Jason Vallotton.

If you are unable to join for the whole conference, day passes are now available. 

August 25-27. Register for in-person, online, and day pass experiences now at bethel.com/braveco. Online registration closes tomorrow August 24 at midnight.

node.text: Sometimes, we find ourselves facing impossible circumstances. Once we come to Christ, it doesn’t mean everything we face is designed by Him. But all things work together for the good of those who love God and are called to His purposes. Often in the Word, when God revealed He was with someone, it was in an impossible circumstance. The key truth we need to live in is that, if we are overwhelmed by the size of our problems—or impossible situations—we have lost sight of the presence of God in our lives. Today, take courage and remind yourself that God is with you, fighting for you and able to do the impossible!

node.text:
Every man faces trials and adversity in life; real battles that form them into all the Lord has created them to be. 

Yet, too often men find themselves uncertain of their own strength, scared of failure, or questioning their purpose in the midst of a battle. Maybe you doubt your own ability or role as a man. The truth is, becoming the man God has destined you to be is a process filled with trial and error, adversity and battle. If you’re in the middle of a battle, questioning if you have what it takes, we want to remind you that you are not alone. You have a heavenly father who is in the foxhole with you. He is a compassionate Father, a force of strength when you feel weak, and the reassurance you need if you fail. 

Men, if you’re hungry to discover the Godly fight within you to face the challenges of life with courage and perseverance, we want to invite you to our first-ever men’s conference. BraveCo Men's Conference is happening in Redding, CA and online next week, August 25-27. 

Our prayer is that you’ll walk away connected to your God-given purpose, poured into as a man, and surrounded by a brotherhood of men willing to get into the foxhole with you.

If you are unable to attend in person this year, the online experience is nothing short of the in-person experience. You will receive one year on-demand access to all video content, exclusive interviews with speakers, and dedicated ministry times. Register for the online experience by August 24th. 

BraveCo Men’s Conference August 25-27. Register for both the in-person and online experience at bethel.com/braveco

node.text:
In one encounter with God, everything can change. Regardless of your background or what you are going through, the God of revival and awakening is ready to meet you right where you are at.

We would love for you to join us for our 7th Annual Young Saints Conference [On-Campus and Online] on October 22-23 as we pursue a fresh encounter so that we may once again chase after all that God has in store for us. It is your destiny, as the youth of this generation, to be awakened again and carry power into the world. Speakers will include Ben Fitzgerald, Tom Crandall, and more! Worship from YS Worship.

node.text: "At that time, the disciples came to ask Jesus, 'Who is considered to be the greatest in heaven’s kingdom realm?' Jesus called a little one to his side and said to them, 'Learn this well: Unless you dramatically change your way of thinking and become teachable like a little child, you will never be able to enter in. Whoever continually humbles himself to become like this little child is the greatest one in heaven’s kingdom realm.'" - Matthew 18:1-4, TPT
